            </div>
            <div class="bg-white px-4 py-2 rounded-lg shadow-sm">
              <span class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-600">Local SEO</span>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white px-4 py-2 rounded-lg shadow-sm">
              <span class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-600"
                >Lead Generation</span
              >
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white px-4 py-2 rounded-lg shadow-sm">
              <span class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-600"
                >Mobile Responsive</span
              >
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Personal Story Section -->
      <div
        class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-lg border border-gray-200 p-8 mb-12"
      >
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center text-gray-900 mb-8">
            My Journey with Web Development
          </h2>
          <div class="prose prose-lg mx-auto text-gray-700">
            <p class="mb-6">
              I've always been fascinated by how things work and how to make
              them better. That's what drew me to fire safety - the precision,
              the attention to detail, the satisfaction of ensuring buildings
              are safe and compliant. Web development is very similar in many
              ways.
            </p>
            <p class="mb-6">
              I started learning to code years ago, initially just to understand
              how websites work. But like fire safety, once you start creating,
              you can't stop. There's something incredibly satisfying about
              writing clean, efficient code and watching it come to life as a
              website that helps businesses connect with their customers.
            </p>
            <p class="mb-6">
              What I love about web development is the same thing I love about
              fire safety - the attention to detail, the problem-solving, and
              the ability to create something that's both beautiful and
              practical. Whether it's ensuring fire doors are compliant or
              building a custom website, the principles are the same: quality
              work, solid construction, and thoughtful design.
            </p>
            <p>
              I've built this website you're looking at right now, along with
              several others for local businesses. Each project is different,
              each has its own challenges, and each gives me the same
              satisfaction as completing a fire safety inspection.
            </p>
